<BLOCKQUOTE>Posted by
<a href="mailto:susan@cal.com">Susan</a> on 4:54:14 12/18/2001 from 63.203.99.45:<p>
In reply to: <a href="http://www.maratsafin.com/msgboard.mv?parm_func=showmsg+parm_msgnum=1004668">What are your predictions for 2001?</a> posted by 
Lucie on 17:28:19 12/17/2001 from 62.252.128.5:<p>
    Hey, Lucie.  You've asked a very provocative question.  I think things are very wide open for next year, and I think many players, including Marat, Andre, Juan-Carlos, Guga, Roger, Andy and Tommy are possibilities for a grand slam.  I also think Tim and Pete are a big possibility for Wimbledon, and that we perhaps shouldn't discount Pete too soon.  He's reportedly stepped up his training and has a new coach and he's, well, Pete, so who knows?  Another GS is within his reach, particularly at Wimbledon.  Lots of people are ready to engrave Tim's name of the Wimbly trophy for 2002, but I think they are a bit premature.  Perhaps there aren't too many grasscourt specialists left, but there are a few who, on a given day, could give Tim or Pete a run for their money.  Marat is one of them, as is Lleyton.  And I think Andy will excel on grass eventually as well.  <br><br>     Of more interesting note than my predictions are those of Sports Illustrated writer Jon Wertheim.  Here's his predictions (of course, he was wrong about a number of his 2001 predictions, as he admits  -- notice that he picked Marat as most likely to finish 2001 as No. 1.  It's interesting that he's picking Juan-Carlos Ferror as most likely to finish No. 1 in 2002, and he's picking Andy as most likely to win his first GS.    <br><br>JON:  FIRST, as promised, some predictions for 2002. In the interest of full disclosure/embarrassment, I've humbly posted my whiffs, I mean, picks for 2001. <br><br>Wins first career title <br><br>Men: Mikhail Youzhny <br>Women: Elena Dementieva <br>2001 picks: Guillermo Coria and Anna Kournikova <br><br>Wins first career Grand Slam <br><br>Men: Andy Roddick <br>Women: Kim Clijsters <br>2001 picks: Magnus Norman and no one. <br><br>Comeback player of the year <br><br>Men: Norman <br>Women: Mary Pierce <br>2001 picks: Marcelo Rios and Pierce <br><br>Lives up to the hype <br><br>Men: Roddick <br>Women: Daja Bedanova <br>2001 picks: Roger Federer and Lina Krasnoroutskaya <br><br>Continues to be all hype <br><br>Men: Todd Reid <br>Women: Ashley Harkleroad <br>2001 picks: Mark Philippoussis and Alexandra Stevenson <br><br>Most likely to retire <br><br>Men: Andre Agassi <br>Women: Arantxa Sánchez-Vicario <br>2001 picks: Pat Rafter and Sánchez-Vicario <br><br>Most likely to make a splash <br><br>Men: Marko Ancic <br>Women: Angelique Widjaja <br>2001 picks: Roddick and Maria Emilia Salerni <br><br>Finishes the year ranked No. 1 <br><br>Men: Juan Carlos Ferrero <br>Women: Venus Williams <br>2001 picks: Marat Safin and Venus Williams <br><br><br>Susan<br><br><br><br><br>     <br><br>     <br><br>      <br><br>      <br>
